solutions.content:
**Explaination:**
Classic 0-1 knapsack variation:
At any index **i** we have 2 choice either to include the current string or not.
let **dp [i][j][k]** denote maximum size subset till **i** having atmost **j** zeroes and **k** ones
1. If we don't include i, we assume our optimal answer comes from i-1 
2. If we include means i,  we have a new subproblem of maxsize subset till **i-1** having atmost j- zeroes(str) abd k-ones(str)
From the above two observations we have the dp formula as
**let z= zeroes in ith string and o as ones in ith string
let optimalAns1 = dp[i-1][j][k] ---- from statement 1
	optimal Ans2 = dp[i-1][j-z][k-o]
	dp[i][j][k] = max(optimal1,optimal2)**
**Time: O(l*m*n)     -> l is number of strings
Space:O(l*m*n)**

**Optimisation**:
At any index i we only need previous state of **i i.e i-1**. So we can use a dp with size 2 instead of length. Since consecutive i's always have opposite parity (if one is odd other is even), we can take %2 to get current and prev state
**Space: O(m*n)**

Use one based indexing for edge case in 0th index as we have to access i-1.
**Hope it helps. DO upvote :)**

```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<vector<int> > > dp;
    int findMaxForm(vector<string>& str, int m, int n) {
        int l=str.size();
        vector<pair<int,int> > cnt(l);
       auto getCount = [&](string s){
            int cnt=0;;
            for(auto c:s) cnt += c-'0';
            return make_pair(s.length()-cnt,cnt);
        };

        for(int i=0;i<l;i++) cnt[i]=getCount(str[i]);

        dp.resize(2);
        for(auto &y:dp){
            y.resize(m+1);
            for(auto &x:y) x.resize(n+1);
        }

        for(int i=1;i<=l;i++){
            int z = cnt[i-1].first , o= cnt[i-1].second;
            for(int j=0;j<=m;j++){
                for(int k=0;k<=n;k++){
                    //if not include
                    dp[i%2][j][k] = dp[(i-1+2)%2][j][k];
                    //if included
                    if(j-z>=0 and k-o >=0){
                        dp[i%2][j][k] = max(dp[i%2][j][k] , 1 + dp[(i-1+2)%2][j-z][k-o]);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[l%2][m][n];
    }
};
```

